Plot detects per subgroup

plot_detects_per_subgroup.Rd

Plot number of detects, partial detects, and nondetects per subgroup

plot_detects_per_subgroup(
  object,
  svar = "subgroup",
  color_values = default_color_values(object, svar)
)

Arguments

object

SummarizedExperiment
svar

svar
color_values

character vector (names = svalues, values = color names)

Value

ggplot object

Examples

# STEMCELLS
    file <- download_data('stemcells.proteinGroups.txt')

#> Use already available file: ~/importomicscache/datasets/stemcells/stemcells.proteinGroups.txt
    invert_subgroups <- c('E_EM', 'E_BM', 'EM_BM')
    object <- read_proteingroups(file, invert_subgroups = invert_subgroups,
                                  impute = FALSE, plot = FALSE)

#> 	Filter features
#> 		Retain 8528/8627 features: ~Reverse != "+"
#> 		Retain 8408/8528 features: contaminant != '+'
#> 		Retain 7877/8408 features: non-zero, non-NA, and non-NaN for some sample
#> 		Standardize snames: Ratio M/L normalized E(L).EM(M).BM(H).R1  ->  E(L).EM(M).BM(H).R1{M/L}
#> 		Demultiplex snames: E(L).EM(M).BM(H).R1{M/L}  ->  EM_E.R1
#> 		Guess subgroup values from sampleids: EM_E.R1 => EM_E
#> 	Transform exprs
#> 		Invert subgroups E_EM, E_BM, EM_BM
#> 			exprs    : 8.47 -> 0.12
#> 			subgroups: E_BM -> BM_E
#> 			sampleids: E_BM.R2 -> BM_E.R2
#> 		Order on subgroup
#> 		Replace NaN -> NA for 6935/70893 values (in 1565/7877 features and 9/9 samples)
#> 		Log2 transform exprs
    plot_detects_per_subgroup(object)
